A8.
 A least upper bound of some set 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 (take LUB
\begin_inset Formula $\in\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

) will be greater than or equal to every element in 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

, and is less than or equal to any other upper bound.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 is to be a least upper bound of 
\begin_inset Formula $\{a_{n}\}_{n\in\mathbb{N}}$
\end_inset

, then we must necessarily have that 
\begin_inset Formula $a\ge a_{i}\in\{a_{n}\}$
\end_inset

.
